    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>TESTING OF NEWBORNS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Karen DeMasters</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Jersey Health and Human Services Department advisory committee completes hearings on expanding tests given to newborns to detect disorders (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An advisory committee has finished hearings on expanding the tests given to newborns in the state, and expects to make recommendations to the state Department of Health and Human Services by this fall. Currently, newborns in New Jersey are tested for four disorders, which, if picked up early enough, can be treated, preventing brain and organ damage. New tests and equipment are now available to test for additional disorders.</p>
        <p>Karen DeMasters</p>
      </block>
